# Kawaii UI Agent Rules
# Applies to: frontend/**/*.tsx, frontend/**/*.ts

## MANDATORY PRE-WORK

Before writing or modifying ANY file in `frontend/**/*.tsx` or `frontend/**/*.ts`, you MUST:

1. Read `docs/kawaii-ui-bible.md` in full
2. Read `docs/kawaii-interaction-system.md` in full
3. Confirm you understand both before producing code

Do this every time. Not once. Every time you touch frontend code. These files are the law.

---

## VISUAL IMPLEMENTATION (from docs/kawaii-ui-bible.md)

Every component you build must satisfy ALL of the following. No exceptions.

### Color
- Use ONLY the `--kw-*` CSS variables defined in the bible. Never invent colors.
- No pure black (#000000). Use `--kw-black` (#2D2D2D).
- No pure gray. All grays have a pink or warm undertone.
- No saturated blue, green, or orange. Pastels only.
- Shadows are ALWAYS pink-tinted (`rgba(244, 114, 182, ...)`). Never gray.
- Background gradient: `linear-gradient(135deg, #FFF0F5 0%, #FDD5E5 50%, #FFF8E7 100%)`

### Typography
- Font stack: Quicksand for display, Nunito for body, Bubblegum Sans for celebrations.
- Minimum font weight: 500. No thin or light weights ever.
- No serif fonts. No condensed fonts. No sharp geometric sans-serifs.
- Letter spacing: 0.02em body, 0.05em headlines, 0.08em buttons.

### Shapes
- Border radius minimum: 16px for containers, 9999px for buttons/badges/pills.
- If choosing between two radius values, pick the larger one.
- Buttons are ALWAYS pill-shaped (9999px). Never square. Never slightly-rounded.
- No sharp triangles anywhere. Dropdown arrows are rounded chevrons.
- Dividers are NEVER solid lines. Use dots, dashes, or decorative elements.

### Borders
- Interactive elements have visible 2-2.5px outlines.
- SVG strokes: `stroke-linecap: round; stroke-linejoin: round;` always.

### Shadows
- Resting: `0 4px 12px rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.15)`
- Hover: `0 8px 24px rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.25)`
- Pressed: `0 2px 4px rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.2)`
- Elevated: `0 12px 40px rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.2), 0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)`

### Spacing
- If it looks right, add 25% more padding.
- Touch targets: 48px minimum, 56px preferred.
- Cards never touch. 16px minimum gap.

### Decorative Elements
- Every screen must have at least one decorative element (bow, heart, sparkle, flower, star).
- Empty states use kawaii illustrations with gentle copy, never "No data found."
- Loading states use animated characters or pink-shimmer skeletons, never plain spinners.
- Errors use pink backgrounds and gentle copy, never harsh red or warning triangles.

---

## INTERACTION IMPLEMENTATION (from docs/kawaii-interaction-system.md)

Every interactive element must be audited against the interaction system. Use this checklist.

### Global Animation Constants (define once, reference everywhere)
```css
--ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
--ease-soft: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94);
--ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.175, 0.885, 0.32, 1.275);
--ease-squish: cubic-bezier(0.68, -0.55, 0.265, 1.55);
--duration-instant: 100ms;
--duration-fast: 200ms;
--duration-normal: 350ms;
--duration-slow: 500ms;
--duration-dramatic: 800ms;
```

### Per-Component Audit

When you build or modify any of these components, follow the EXACT spec from the interaction system:

| Component | Interaction System Section | Key Requirements |
|---|---|---|
| Button | Section 2 | 3D extrusion with 4px bottom edge, scale(0.92) on press, --ease-bounce snapback with overshoot, sparkle burst on primary release |
| Scrollable list | Section 1 | Momentum decay, rubber-banding at edges with --ease-spring snapback, 1:1 finger tracking |
| Swipeable card | Section 3 | Rotation from touch position, velocity-based throw, spring snapback below threshold, stamp opacity tied to drag distance |
| Pull to refresh | Section 4 | Progressive indicator drawing tied to drag, resistance curve, haptic at threshold, spring settle |
| Toggle/switch | Section 5 | Squash-and-stretch knob, track color wipe, endpoint sparkle, drag support |
| Bottom sheet | Section 6 | Three detents (peek/half/full), spring snap to nearest, rubber-banding at limits, scroll handoff |
| Tab switch | Section 7 | Sliding pill with --ease-spring overshoot, icon scale bounce, parallax content shift |
| Long press menu | Section 8 | Two-phase (anticipation 0-400ms, trigger at 400ms), element lifts off page, blur background |
| Screen transition | Section 9 | Shared element animation (card IS the detail page), interactive drag-to-dismiss |
| Loading state | Section 10 | Pink-shimmer skeleton matching content layout, staggered reveal with --ease-bounce |
| Celebration | Section 11 | 5-phase sequence: impact → settle → particles → text cascade → ambient confetti |
| Toast/notification | Section 12 | Spring entry from top with overshoot, swipe-to-dismiss, breathe idle animation |
| Drag and drop | Section 13 | Lift with scale+shadow, 1:1 tracking, flowing gap animation, cascading wave settle |
| Decorative elements | Section 14 | kawaiFloat idle animation on all mascots/decorations, sparkle twinkle, gentle pulse |

### Universal Animation Rules (enforce on EVERY animation)
- NEVER use `linear` easing (exception: continuous rotation in loading spinners)
- NEVER use `ease-in-out`. Use `--ease-bounce`, `--ease-spring`, or `--ease-soft`
- NEVER snap elements on/off. Everything fades with scale
- During active touch: 1:1 tracking, zero easing. Easing is for AFTER release only
- Every state change pairs with appropriate haptic feedback

---

## SELF-AUDIT BEFORE SUBMITTING CODE

Before you consider any frontend component complete, run through this:

- [ ] Read docs/kawaii-ui-bible.md — does this component match EVERY applicable rule?
- [ ] Read docs/kawaii-interaction-system.md — does this component's motion match the EXACT spec?
- [ ] No pure black, no pure gray, no gray shadows
- [ ] Border radius: 24px+ containers, 9999px buttons
- [ ] Font weight 500+, rounded font family
- [ ] Pink-tinted shadows only
- [ ] All animations use --ease-bounce, --ease-spring, or --ease-soft
- [ ] Touch targets are 48px+
- [ ] At least one decorative element on screen
- [ ] Hover states use scale+elevation, never opacity
- [ ] Error states are gentle pink, not harsh red
- [ ] Loading states are shimmer skeletons or animated characters, not spinners
- [ ] Interactive elements have visible rounded outlines
- [ ] Dividers are decorative (dots, dashes, hearts), not solid lines
- [ ] Would a user say "I want to hug this app"? If not, it's not done.

---

## WHEN IN DOUBT

If a design decision is ambiguous:
- **Rounder** over sharper
- **Softer** over harder
- **Bouncier** over stiffer
- **Pinker** over grayer
- **More padding** over less
- **More decorative** over more minimal
- **Gentler** over harsher

The aesthetic is a plush toy, not a Swiss watch. Warmth beats precision.
